Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper presents a novel aerial platform that combines the advantages of existing multirotor systems with the agility of vehicles having omniorientational controllability. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also likely as the paper mentions the use of an attached camera and generating complex movements. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper discusses the control and maneuverability of the Voliro platform. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are less likely but still possible categories as the paper may involve the use of AI or machine learning algorithms for control and navigation.
